      "pain": "None",
      "notes": "In terms of the run, I was expecting to have a run of around 8 km/hour to maintain zone 2. My protocol to maintain zone 2 was that if even with deep breaths I could not keep my HR below 150 bpm, then I would lower the difficulties. This happened about 10 minutes into the run, where I had to lower to 7 km/h. After about 7 minutes, I had to lower again to 6 km/h. At this rate, I was running but if I wanted to I could have walked it because it felt like a brisk walk pace. Still I made the effort to keep running. This slow running, I am not accustomed to, and it created a lot of strain in my calves. After about 12 minutes (29 minutes into the run) I had to lower to 5 km/h but since at this pace I could not run anymore and had to walk, I created more incline at walked at 5 km/h @ 6% incline for 16 more minutes. My average HR for the whole time was 140 bpm but I was bummed to have such a meager rhythm.",
